Third Department,

October, 1966

(October 18, 1966) In the Matter of Daniel E. Button, Appellant, v. Thomas F. Donohue et al., Constituting the Board of Elections of Albany County, Respondents.

Order affirmed, without costs. (See Matter of Battista v. Power, 16 N Y 2d 198; Matter of Lazer v. McNab, 19 A D 2d 830, affd. 13 N Y 2d 935.) Stay vacated. Application for permission to appeal to the Court of Appeals granted. Gibson, P. J., Herlihy, Reynolds, Aulisi and Staley, Jr., JJ., concur.
